HEADWORD: Hatching
<hw>Hatch"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See 1st <er>Hatch</er>.]</ety>
<def>A mode of execution in engraving, drawing, and miniature painting,
in which shading is produced by lines crossing each other at angles more
or less acute; -- called also
<altname>crosshatching</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hatchment</ent>⟦br⟧
